@FullyTested
public enum FileType
extends Enum<FileType>

Classification for files: NORMAL_FILE and DIRECTORY. Currently, Java 6 has no further file types, but this may increase in future versions.

For Windows users, the term "file" may be ambiguous. UNIX terminology refers to all file system entries as files with classifications such as block special, character special, directory, regular, symbolic link, named pipe, and socket.

Author:
Kevin Connor ARPE (kevinarpe@gmail.com)

Enum Constant Detail

NORMAL_FILE

public static final FileType NORMAL_FILE
Files with this type return true from method File.isFile().

The term "normal" is particular to Java. In UNIX terminology, usually "regualar" is used, but the Java filesystem interface is limited to two file types: directories and non-directories. This type refers to non-directories.

DIRECTORY, is(File), from(File)
